==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
A commercial space devoted to sewing and community building.  A sewing lounge generally includes sewing machines available for on-site rental, sewing equipment, fabrics, cutting tables, a local designer boutique, and expert instruction availability.  A sewing lounge also seeks to foster the sewing community through promoting local designers, holding sewing-related classes, community events, and reaching out to the non-sewing community to promote the enjoyment and appreciation of making one's own apparel and accessories.